article.description: Jimmy Hall and Deon Edwin combined to score 35 points as Kent State closed out the nonconference portion of its schedule with a 104-58 rout of Division III Oberlin College Saturday night.
article.headline: Kent State routs Oberlin in nonconference finale, 104-58
article.linkText: Kent State routs Oberlin in nonconference finale, 104-58
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Jimmy Hall and Deon Edwin combined to score 35 points as Kent State closed out the nonconference portion of its schedule with a 104-58 rout of Division III Oberlin College Saturday night. Kent State (9-4) is now 3-1 all-time in the series. Oberlin won the last meeting, 62-60 during the 1945-46 season. The Golden Flashes pulled away steadily in the first half. Khaliq Spicer's dunk with 11 seconds left in the first half sent Kent State into intermission with a 48-23 lead. Hall led the Golden Flashes with 18 points on 9 of 11 shooting from the field. Edwin was 7 of 10, including 1 of 3 from deep, for 17 points. Kent State shot 56.5 percent from the field (39 of 69), including 6 of 18 from beyond the arc. Nathan Cohen scored 19 points to lead the Yoemen, who committed 19 turnovers.
